Photo, COLOR, Shrimp-and-squid pasta.; Photo, COLOR, Traditional Japanese soba 
(buckwheat) noodles are stir-fried with meat and vegetables and garnished with 
seaweed and ginger.; Photo, Masao Shinkai of Horai Tei Japanese-Chinese 
restaurant in Little Tokyo displays seafood chow mein, at left, and Yaki Soba, 
at right. JAVIER MENDOZA / Los Angeles Times; Photo, COLOR, At the Atlas Bar 
&amp; Grill the pad Thai noodles are topped with peanuts and grilled marinated 
shrimp for an unusual pasta meal. ; Photo, Mario Tamayo poses with Southeast 
Asian noodles, called pad Thai, as prepared at his eclectic Atlas Bar &amp; 
Grill in Los Angeles. ANACLETO RAPPING / Los Angeles Times; Photo, COLOR, Penne 
is tossed with sauted asparagus, garlic and tomatoes to make this simple, 
nutritious meal at Giuseppe! restaurant. ; Photo, Giuseppe Bellisario of 
Giuseppe! presents light angel hair pasta with tomatoes and basil at left, and, 
penne with asparagus, at right. THOMAS KELSEY / Los Angeles Times; Photo, Thai 
Peanut Pesto, above, made by blending peanuts with soy sauce and honey, is 
added to bow tie pasta, while another light pasta, below, contains tomatoes. 
</P>
