<LENGTH>
<P>
100 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: SANTA PAULA; 
</P>
<P>
IMPOUNDED GUNS TO BE AUCTIONED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JANET BERGAMO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
About 75 firearms impounded by Santa Paula authorities since last July will be 
sold at public auction, rather than destroyed. 
</P>
<P>
"My interest is in timesaving," Police Chief Walter Adair said. "The sale will 
be more efficient." 
</P>
<P>
While selling the guns will contribute little cash to the city, Adair said, the 
new procedure will prove more economical for Santa Paula. 
</P>
<P>
The City Council authorized the new procedures earlier this week. 
</P>
<P>
Auctioneer Roger Ernst said the city can recoup 75% of the proceeds from guns 
that are sold, usually to gunsmiths who use their parts for repair. JANET 
BERGAMO 
</P>
</TEXT>
