<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN CLEMENTE ISLAND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Navy public works personnel spilled about 1,500 gallons of diesel fuel into the 
Pacific near San Clemente Island on Wednesday, the Navy reported. 
</P>
<P>
The spill, which apparently took place at 12:30 p.m. while workers were 
transferring fuel to a truck on the Navy-owned island, was not near any 
environmentally sensitive areas, the Navy said. About 95% of the fuel 
evaporated by late Wednesday afternoon, said the Navy. 
</P>
<P>
San Clemente Island is about 60 miles northwest of San Diego. 
</P>
