<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN ARRESTED IN BOMB THREAT CASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Reseda man has been arrested in connection with a bomb threat Tuesday that 
forced the evacuation of several buildings and clogged morning traffic in Van 
Nuys, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Carlos Deveraux, 36, was arrested at his home at 6:40 p.m. Tuesday, 10 hours 
after he allegedly called police and told them that he had left seven nuclear 
warheads in a brown Datsun parked outside the Church on the Way in the 14300 
block of Sherman Way, Detective Bob Muldrew said. 
</P>
<P>
Police found no explosives in the car. 
</P>
<P>
Muldrew said police traced the car, which was spray-painted with the number "7" 
and the words "Hot" and "The End," to Deveraux, who attended the church 
occasionally. 
</P>
<P>
Deveraux confessed to police that he had called in the bomb threat, Muldrew 
said. No motive was established. 
</P>
<P>
"He just doesn't know what he's doing," Muldrew said. 
</P>
<P>
Deveraux was scheduled to be arraigned this morning in Van Nuys Municipal 
Court. 
</P>
