<P>
DIGEST /LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 3 ARRESTED IN DEATH OF LANCASTER MAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three Lancaster residents were arrested Wednesday on suspicion of killing a 
Lancaster man whose body was found near the Antelope Valley Freeway last month, 
Los Angeles County sheriff's deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
Deputies raided the residences of Kenneth Massi, 33; George Costello, 34, and 
Christopher Dixon, 28 -- who live in separate units of the same Lancaster 
apartment complex -- and arrested the three men after finding evidence linking 
them to the slaying of Kyle McCabe, 29, Deputy Bill Linnemeyer said. 
</P>
<P>
McCabe's body was found about 200 yards east of the Antelope Valley Freeway 
near G Street on March 12. He had been shot several times and stabbed 
repeatedly in the upper body, Linnemeyer said. 
</P>
<P>
Linnemeyer would not release further details about the case or the nature of 
the evidence recovered in the search. 
</P>
<P>
The suspects were being held without bail at the Antelope Valley Sheriff's 
Station and were scheduled to be arraigned today in Antelope Valley Municipal 
Court. 
</P>
