<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST /LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: PANEL OKS BILL ON METRO RAIL EXTENSION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Assembly Ways and Means Committee approved a bill Wednesday to require 
underground construction of an extension of Metro Rail through residential 
North Hollywood and Van Nuys. 
</P>
<P>
An aide to Sen. Alan Robbins (D-Tarzana), who introduced the measure, said it 
could be considered by the full Assembly as early as today. 
</P>
<P>
Under Robbins' proposal, approved 19 to 0 by the committee, 3.6 miles of the 
Metro Rail extension would be underground along a Southern Pacific railroad 
right of way, partly following Chandler Boulevard between the Hollywood Freeway 
and Hazeltine Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
Residents have protested proposals to place the line above ground because they 
say it would divide neighborhoods and increase noise. 
</P>
