<HEADLINE>
<P>
MANHATTAN BEACH TO HONOR MANAGER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Manhattan Beach will honor City Manager David J. Thompson at a dinner next week 
to mark his retirement from a post he's held for 16 years. He's scheduled to 
leave the job May 1. 
</P>
<P>
The City Council is interviewing candidates to replace Thompson and may name 
his replacement as early as next week. 
</P>
<P>
Thompson, 60, has been city manager since 1974. In a recent interview, he said 
the highlight of his tenure was supervising the transformation in the late 
1970s of a 187-acre Chevron U.S.A. Inc. tank farm into the complex that 
includes the Manhattan Village Mall, 540 homes and the Raddison Hotel. 
</P>
<P>
The $38 dinner is April 14 at 6:30 p.m. at the Raddison. People are asked to 
sign up by Friday by calling the city Administrative and Community Services 
Department at 545-5621, Ext. 362. 
