<P>
Picasso Auction Raises AIDS Funds: The sale in London of four Pablo Picasso 
drawings donated by American photographer Douglas Duncan raised $127,100 for 
Romanian children suffering from AIDS, Christie's auctioneers said Wednesday. 
Duncan donated the drawings on behalf of the U.S. welfare group Americares, 
which has been sending medical relief to Romania. SHAUNA SNOW 
</P>
