<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Kenneth Williams 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Charles Desmarais, director of the Laguna Art Museum, has accepted an 
invitation to join the Assn. of Art Museum Directors, a prestigious New 
York-based professional organization with about 150 members in the United 
States and Canada. Membership in the association is determined by the quality 
of museums' collections and programs as well as directors' achievements. 
</P>
<P>
Desmarais appears to be the only member from Orange County. Kevin E. Consey, 
former Newport Harbor Art Museum director, transferred his membership when he 
was named director of the Chicago Museum of Contemporary Art last year. 
</P>
<P>
Eleven Orange County artists have applied for Artists-in-Residence grants from 
the California Arts Council, nine more than applied last year. A council 
official largely credited Orange County artist Mary-Linn Hughes with the 
increase. Hughes, last year's sole artists-in-residence grant recipient from 
the county, waged a grant awareness campaign of sorts and helped organize a 
recent workshop on how to apply for the grants, which pay artists to work in 
schools and other community agencies. They are awarded in June. 
</P>
</TEXT>
