<TEXT>
<P>
Estefan Leaves Hospital: Singer Gloria Estefan, promising she would soon be 
back performing at 100%, left New York's Orthopedic Institute Hospital for 
Joint Disease on Wednesday, two weeks after a bus crash broke her spine. 
Estefan, 32, faced reporters, cameras and hospital workers from a wheelchair, 
but then ended her news conference by standing, unaided. Doctors have estimated 
her full recovery could take up to six months. SHAUNA SNOW 
</P>
