<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: ART 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SHAUNA SNOW, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chagall Record Set: An unidentified Japanese telephone bidder paid an auction 
record price of $6.09 million for a work by artist Marc Chagall. 
</P>
<P>
The 1949 painting, "The Bride Under the Canopy," was the highest-priced work in 
Tuesday night's sale of Impressionist and modern art at Sotheby's. The painting 
shows a bride and bridegroom under an awning, with a large vase of leaves and 
flowers and a violinist. Another Chagall, "The Farmers' Bouquet," went for 
$5.02 million, also to a Japanese telephone bidder. SHAUNA SNOW 
</P>
</TEXT>
