<HEADLINE>
<P>
TURKEY FRANKS WITH FLAVOR OF THE SOUTHWEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Instead of a beef frankfurter use turkey for lower fat content. And instead of 
using the usual bun, update it with a Southwestern flavor. 
</P>
<P>
Wrap the frankfurter in a flour tortilla. Skip the mustard and relish and use 
shredded cheese, green onions and a zesty salsa. 
</P>
<P>
Turkey frankfurters can be wrapped in cheese slices, such as Swiss, Jack or 
Cheddar, place in frankfurter buns and heated in a microwave. 
</P>
<P>
For a turkey frankfurter casserole, layer the bottom of a casserole with beans 
and top with frankfurters and garnish each with slices of cheese. Bake until 
heated through and cheese is bubbly. 
</P>
<P>
For appetizers, cut frankfurters in halves and spear rounded ends on bamboo 
sticks. Dip in French dressing mixed with mustard and bake until heated 
through. 
</P>
<P>
TURKEY FRANKFURTER ROLL-UPS 
</P>
<P>
4 turkey frankfurters 
</P>
<P>
4 flour tortillas 
</P>
<P>
1 cup shredded Cheddar or Jack cheese 
</P>
<P>
3 green onions, chopped 
</P>
<P>
1/2 cup salsa, mild or hot 
</P>
<P>
Place 1 turkey frankfurter in center of each tortilla. Top each with 1/4 of 
cheese, green onions and salsa. Roll up. Place seam side down on 
microwave-proof platter. Microwave 1 minute on HIGH. Makes 4 servings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, TURKEY FRANKFURTER ROLL-UPS 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
