COMMUNITY DIGEST : LONG BEACH; 
</P>
<P>
GRAFFITI INFORMATION COULD BRING $1,000 REWARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tips about your neighborhood graffiti artist could be worth $1,000 under Long 
Beach's graffiti reward program. 
</P>
<P>
The City Council recently doubled the reward for information that leads to the 
arrest and conviction of any person maliciously destroying property by defacing 
it with graffiti. The reward, originally $300 when the program was established 
in 1986, had risen to $500 and then was increased to $1,000 late last month. 
</P>
<P>
People with information about graffiti violations can call the 24-hour graffiti 
reward hot line, 420-3486. Information will be kept confidential. To report 
graffiti that needs to be removed, call 432-8904, Ext. 2215. 
</P>
