COMMUNITY DIGEST : SOUTH GATE; 
</P>
<P>
YOUTHS TO MARCH FRIDAY AGAINST DRUGS, GANGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
More than 4,500 students plan to march Friday in an anti-drug and anti-gang 
rally sponsored by the South Gate Commission on Youth. 
</P>
<P>
The march will start at 9:15 a.m. at South Gate Junior High School, 4100 
Firestone Blvd., and proceed to South Gate Park, 4900 Southern Ave., about a 
mile away. 
</P>
<P>
At the park, students will view display booths showing alternative activities 
to gang and drug involvement. These will include bands, drill teams, football 
and soccer teams and folkloric groups. 
</P>
<P>
To caution students not to drink and drive, wrecked cars will be displayed. 
</P>
<P>
Participating students will be from South Gate Junior High, South Gate High 
School and nine area elementary schools. The schools are part of the Los 
Angeles Unified School District. 
</P>
<P>
The Commission on Youth is composed of volunteers from business, the schools, 
churches, city government and parents. 
