<HEADLINE>
<P>
NERVE GAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Morality over money! How refreshing to read (Part A, March 28) that two 
chemical firms, Occidental and Mobay, have refused to sell the ingredients of 
nerve gas to the mighty Pentagon itself! I hope some edict doesn't force them 
to "say uncle." They are saving us from the universal opprobrium we would merit 
if we resumed manufacture of chemical weapons while purportedly negotiating a 
worldwide ban. 
</P>
<P>
HELEN L. TRAVIS 
</P>
<P>
San Pedro 
</P>
