<TEXT>
<P>
A review panel for The Athletics Congress, U.S. track and field's governing 
body, lifted the two-year suspension of Texas A&amp;M sprinter Andre Cason. 
</P>
<P>
TAC suspended Cason last week for failing to report for a drug test. Four-time 
Olympian steeplechaser Henry Marsh was suspended Tuesday for a similar offense. 
</P>
<P>
Also, TAC suspended UCLA horizontal jumper McArthur Anderson for three months 
because he tested positive for a banned substance. 
</P>
<P>
