<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: SANTA MONICA; 
</P>
<P>
WEST END OF PIER TO REOPEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The west end of the Santa Monica Pier, which was destroyed by heavy storms in 
1983, will reopen Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Festivities start at 12:30 p.m., when Mayor Dennis Zane and other city 
officials parade to the pier from the 3rd Street Promenade at Broadway, 
accompanied by the Santa Monica High School marching band. 
</P>
<P>
The celebration will continue Saturday with a free jazz concert featuring 
Conrad Janis and the Unlisted Beverly Hills Jazz Band from noon to 6 p.m. 
Refreshments will be sold at 1940 prices from noon to 2 p.m., free carousel 
rides for children will be offered all day, and a fireworks salute will be held 
at 7:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
The entire pier is undergoing a $34.8-million redevelopment. When completed in 
the summer of 1992, it will include nightclubs, restaurants, retail shops and 
additional rides. 
</P>
</TEXT>
