<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: PASADENA; 
</P>
<P>
HEARING ON NORTHWEST PLAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Residents of Northwest Pasadena will give city officials their opinions and 
ideas at 9:30 a.m. Saturday at the Jackie Robinson Park gymnasium, 1081 N. Fair 
Oaks Ave. 
</P>
<P>
The city's Northwest Task Force is holding a second public hearing as part of 
its evaluation of the city's Northwest Plan, a five-year project to improve the 
city's predominantly minority community. Ideas will be sought on how the area 
of the city has fared in economic development, employment, public safety, the 
environment and human services, such as police and fire protection and 
recreation programs. 
</P>
<P>
A final hearing will be held April 28 before the task force presents its 
findings to the Board of Directors. 
</P>
