<HEADLINE>
<P>
GRAND METROPOLITAN COOKS UP CAKE DEAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MINNEAPOLIS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Grand Metropolitan PLC said it has reached agreement with Dalgety PLC regarding 
the exchange of its Hammonds Sauce and Greens Cake Mix businesses in return for 
Dalgety's Memory Lane Cakes business. 
</P>
<P>
Completion of the agreement is expected in early April, the company said. 
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, Dalgety will pay Grand Metropolitan a cash adjustment of 
$4.48 million. 
</P>
<P>
Memory Lane has sales of about $57 million compared to sales of $49 million for 
the businesses of Greens and Hammonds. 
</P>
<P>
The business will be integrated into Grand Metropolitan Foods Europe, the 
European food division of Grand Metropolitan Food Sector. 
</P>
</TEXT>
