<P>
HUBBLE TELESCOPE READY TO ORBIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CAPE CANAVERAL, Fla. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Engineers belatedly completed critical testing of the $1.5-billion Hubble Space 
Telescope early today with forecasters predicting an 80% chance of good weather 
for the shuttle Discovery's blastoff Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
"We're go. We're on schedule for April 10," said NASA spokeswoman Lisa Malone. 
"It's looking good." 
</P>
<P>
Discovery's countdown to launch the year's third shuttle mission is scheduled 
to begin at 3 p.m. Saturday, about an hour after the ship's five-member crew 
arrives at Kennedy Space Center from Houston. 
</P>
</TEXT>
