W. GERMAN MISSILE REMOVAL SET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WUESCHHEIM, West Germany 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The U.S. Air Force will remove its first nuclear Cruise missiles from West 
Germany next week, a spokesman said today. 
</P>
<P>
All Cruise missiles in Western Europe are to be scrapped by May next year under 
a 1987 U.S.-Soviet treaty to cut intermediate-range nuclear forces. 
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the first 16 of 96 missiles in West Germany, all based at 
Wueschheim Air Station south of Coblenz, will be removed next Wednesday and 
shipped to a U.S. air base in Arizona where they will be destroyed. 
