<P>
CUPERTINO, Calif. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tandem Computers Inc.'s stock price fell sharply today after the company 
disappointed investors with news that its earnings for the fiscal second 
quarter ended March 31 will be lower than expected. 
</P>
<P>
In early trading, Tandem shares were down 12%, or $3.25, to $24. It was the 
most active issue on the New York Stock Exchange. 
</P>
<P>
Industry analysts previously predicted 1990 would be a big year for the 
Cupertino-based computer maker, whose product rollouts will be massive this 
year. 
</P>
<P>
However, the impressive lineup is making its debut amid an industry slowdown. 
Many major U.S. computer makers' earnings have been dented by weaker sales and 
heated competition. 
